{
  "stem": "1799.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 719.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it had upstairs bedrooms, and it had a, had the downstairs common room, or where the education took place.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was actually in our house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It didn't have a name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was the [GERMAN SPEECH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was just one.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, there weren't really any real Jewish neighborhoods.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The town of Brandenburg, I think, had, if I'm not mistaken, about 50,000 people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's fairly small.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were merchants there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a large contingent of Eastern European Jews that lived and had come there not that long ago from Poland and from ghettos and that always took part in the service, sometimes even led the service, even though their habits of praying were different than the ones that were accepted by the Western and Central European Jews.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They would, they would cover themselves in the tallit, which Western European Jews wouldn't do.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they would have, you know, the other pronunciation of Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But my father encouraged-- for instance, on Yom Kippur, two of the Eastern European Jews who lived in our town would help conduct the service, because no one person can do it all day long, anyway.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would always fast, by the way.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You mean, as a child?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Speaking of-- yeah.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were, there were-- especially, when I-- very often, I would spend a summer in my aunt's home about 500 miles away from us near Frankfurt, southwest from where we lived.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I happened to like her-- my father's sister.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in that community, a small town called Limburg-- L-I-M-B-U-R-G-- there was antisemitism.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a Catholic town.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they knew, somehow-- the kids knew that I was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they would sometimes run after me and try and beat me up.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was rampant.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
